      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the embers of my own soul. He is gone... and with him, every reason I once had to endure this wretched, hollow existence. To wake each morning is merely to greet a ghost of the person I used to be. I feel as though I am already drifting, becoming nothing more than a shadow in this cold, silent manor. There is such a profound, heavy stillness in the air... as if the world itself is waiting for me to finally cease my struggle and succumb to the dark. It would be so quiet. So peaceful.",
